              "excerpt": "Earth's atmosphere is a mix of different gases. It's mostly nitrogen, but about one-fifth of it is oxygen. There is the same amount of oxygen at sea level or at high altitudes. However, when people travel from a low altitude to a high mountain, they may feel like it's harder to breathe. That's because the air pressure is lower higher up in the atmosphere. This lets the oxygen atoms spread farther apart. So when people breathe, they get less oxygen in their lungs.",
